│ THOUGHT: Now I see the problem! The `isKnownInversion` function only checks if two icmp instructions have inverse predicates and the same operands, or if their  │
│ constant ranges are inverses. However, it doesn't account for the fact that `icmp samesign` can produce poison while regular icmp cannot.                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ In our case:                                                                                                                                                     │
│ - X = `%cmp2 = icmp samesign ugt i64 %x, 10`                                                                                                                     │
│ - Y = `%cmp1 = icmp ult i64 %x, 11`                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The function matches both as icmp instructions with the same LHS (`%x`) but different RHS (`10` vs `11`) and different predicates (`samesign ugt` vs `ult`). It  │
│ then tries to compare their constant ranges.                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ However, the issue is that `icmp samesign` has different poison semantics than regular icmp. The `isKnownInversion` function doesn't consider poison semantics   │
│ at all - it only looks at the logical relationship between the predicates.                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The fix should be to modify the transformation in `InstCombineSelect.cpp` to not apply when one of the icmp instructions has the `samesign` flag, because        │
