│ THOUGHT: Now I see the issue! There are test cases like `test_select_inverse_samesign_both` and `test_select_inverse_samesign_both_rhsc_same_sign` that have     │
│ BOTH icmp instructions with samesign, and the test expects them to be transformed to XOR.                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ But according to my reasoning, if both icmp instructions have samesign, then they should have the same poison behavior - either both are poison or both are not  │
│ poison. In that case, the transformation might be safe.                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ Let me reconsider the poison semantics:                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ - If both icmp instructions have samesign, then they will both be poison under the same conditions (when the operands have different signs).                     │
│ - If both are poison, then the select returns poison regardless of the condition.                                                                                │
│ - If both are not poison, then they have inverse boolean values, so the XOR transformation is valid.                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ So my fix is too conservative! I should only prevent the transformation when exactly ONE of the icmp instructions has samesign, not when both do.                │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The correct condition should be:                                                                                                                                 │
│ - If neither has samesign: OK to transform                                                                                                                       │
│ - If both have samesign: OK to transform (same poison semantics)                                                                                                 │
│ - If exactly one has samesign: NOT OK to transform (different poison semantics)                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ Let me update my helper function and condition accordingly.                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                          │
│ # Update the helper function to check if exactly one has samesign                                                                                                │
│ sed -i '52c\                                                                                                                                                     │
│ static bool hasMismatchedSameSign(Value *V1, Value *V2) {\                                                                                                       │
│   bool HasSS1 = false, HasSS2 = false;\                                                                                                                          │
│   if (auto *ICmp1 = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(V1))\                                                                                                                     │
│     HasSS1 = ICmp1->hasSameSign();\                                                                                                                              │
│   if (auto *ICmp2 = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(V2))\                                                                                                                     │
│     HasSS2 = ICmp2->hasSameSign();\                                                                                                                              │
│   return HasSS1 != HasSS2;\                                                                                                                                      │
│ }' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                              │
